LINUX COMMANDS â€” COMPLETE PRACTICAL LIST
1. Basic File & Directory Commands
Command	Description
ls	List directory contents
ls -l	Long listing (permissions, owner, size)
ls -a	Show hidden files
pwd	Print current working directory
cd	Change directory
cd ..	Go up one level
mkdir	Create directory
rmdir	Remove empty directory
rm -r	Delete directory + contents
cp	Copy files
mv	Move/rename files
touch	Create empty file
cat	View file content
nl	View file with line numbers
head	Show first 10 lines
tail	Show last 10 lines
tail -f	Live file monitoring (logs)
2. File Permissions & Ownership
Command	Description
chmod	Change file permissions
chmod 755 file	rwxr-xr-x
chown user file	Change owner
chown user:group file	Change owner + group
umask	Default permissions mask
3. File Search & Filtering
Command	Description
find /path -name filename	Search files by name
locate name	Fast search using DB
grep "text" file	Search text inside file
grep -i	Case-insensitive
grep -r	Recursive search
awk	Text processing
sed	Stream editor (replace text)
4. File Compression & Archiving
Command	Description
tar -cvf	Create archive
tar -xvf	Extract archive
gzip	Compress
gunzip	Decompress
zip file.zip file	Zip
unzip file.zip	Unzip
5. System Information
Command	Description
uname -a	System info
hostname	Show hostname
top	Real-time tasks
htop	Improved top
uptime	System load & uptime
df -h	Disk usage
du -sh folder	Folder size
free -h	Memory usage
whoami	Current user
id	User/group IDs
lsblk	List block devices
lscpu	CPU info
6. Package Management
Debian / Ubuntu
Command	Description
apt update	Refresh repo
apt upgrade	Upgrade packages
apt install package	Install package
apt remove package	Remove package
dpkg -i file.deb	Install .deb
RedHat / CentOS / Fedora
Command	Description
yum install package	Install
yum update	Update
dnf install package	Modern version
rpm -ivh file.rpm	Install rpm
7. Process Management
Command	Description
ps	Show processes
ps aux	All processes
kill PID	Kill process
kill -9 PID	Force kill
pgrep	Find process ID
pkill	Kill by name
systemctl start service	Start service
systemctl stop service	Stop service
systemctl status service	Status
8. User & Group Management
Command	Description
useradd user	Add user
passwd user	Add password
userdel user	Delete user
groupadd group	Create group
usermod -aG group user	Add user to group
su user	Switch user
sudo	Run as admin
9. Networking Commands
Command	Description
ifconfig	Show IP (older)
ip a	Show IP (modern)
ping	Test connectivity
curl	Make web requests
wget	Download files
netstat -tulnp	List ports
ss -tulnp	Modern port tool
scp file user@ip:/path	Secure copy
ssh user@ip	SSH login
nmcli	Network manager
10. Disk / Storage Commands
Command	Description
mount	Mount device
umount	Unmount
fdisk -l	Disk partitions
mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdx	Format disk
parted	Partition tool
blkid	Block device IDs
11. Logs & Monitoring
Command	Description
journalctl	System logs
journalctl -u service	Logs for service
/var/log/auth.log	Authentication logs
/var/log/syslog	System logs
dmesg	Kernel logs
12. Networking & Security
Command	Description
iptables	Firewall rules
ufw enable	Simple firewall
ufw status	Firewall status
fail2ban-client	Ban attackers
13. Editing Files
Editor	Usage
nano file	Easy editor
vi file	Open with vi
vim file	Advanced editor
14. Shell Commands / Misc
Command	Description
echo	Print text
history	Show command history
clear	Clear terminal
alias	Command shortcut
date	Show date/time
cal	Calendar
